# ==============================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# ==============================================
# This project uses EAS Secrets for production credentials
# Never commit files containing:
# - API keys, tokens, or passwords
# - Apple Developer certificates (.p12, .cer, .mobileprovision)
# - Android signing keys (.jks, .keystore except debug.keystore)
# - Database credentials
# - OAuth client secrets
#
# For local development:
# 1. Copy .env.example to .env
# 2. Fill in development/test credentials
# 3. Never commit .env with real keys
#
# For production:
# Use EAS Secrets: eas secret:create --scope project --name KEY_NAME --value "value"
